       =20
  [1] I mean, in a normal company, if you sign an open letter threatening t=
o quit, management might reasonably decide to fire you even if you change y=
our mind. But since virtually all of OpenAI=E2=80=99s employees (and manage=
rs!) signed the letter, and artificial intelligence researchers are in high=
 demand, that would not have been a realistic option for OpenAI.


  [2] That is, this one,   the one over the summer at a $150 billion valuat=
ion, and another one in January at $137 billion. I=E2=80=99m not sure this =
one will get done by the end of the year, or be for $750 million, but you g=
et the idea.


  [3] The traditional  life cycle theory is that you live below your means =
in middle age, and beyond your means in youth and old age. But in practice =
in old age this often means living beyond your *income* by spending down ba=
nk deposits, while in youth you don=E2=80=99t have bank deposits to spend d=
own so you take out loans.


  [4] Similarly, if everyone in your town is young, you will be able to mak=
e good credit decisions but won=E2=80=99t have any money to lend, so you=E2=
=80=99ll have to hop on the train to the big city with an empty bucket and =
try to borrow the money from a big bank.


  [5] In my day it was called R. R. Donnelley & Sons, which later  spun off=
 its financial printer business into Donnelley Financial Solutions. In my d=
ay, though, Donnelley was one of several competing printers; the business i=
s more consolidated now.


  [6] A realistic possibility is "hello, I was just interviewed by the FBI =
and worry I'm going to be arrested any minute now, can I hire you?" Less fu=
nny than the other ones.


