-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">OpenAI bluff</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/33617633.284401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9vcGVu=
YWktZW1wbG95ZWVzLWRpZC1ub3Qtd2FudC10by13b3JrLWZvci1taWNyb3NvZnQtMjAyMy0xMj9=
1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1TYWlsdGhydSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249SW=
5zaWRlcl9Ub2RheQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB200c1631" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">No kidding</a>:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After Sam Altman was fired from OpenAI late la=
st month, the startup's employees threatened to leave and accept a blanket =
offer from Microsoft to hire them all.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This was an audacious bluff and most staffers =
had no real interest in working for Microsoft, several current and former e=
mployees told Business Insider. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One current OpenAI employee admitted that, des=
pite nearly everyone on staff signing up to follow Altman out the door, "No=
 one wanted to go to Microsoft." This person called the company "the bigges=
t and slowest" of all the major tech companies =E2=80=94 the exact opposite=
 of how OpenAI employees see their startup.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Given the absence of interest in joining Micro=
soft, many OpenAI employees "felt pressured" to sign the open letter, the e=
mployee admitted. The letter itself was drafted by a group of longtime staf=
fers who have the most clout and money at stake with years of industry stan=
ding and equity built up, as well as higher pay. They began calling other s=
taffers late on Sunday night, urging them to sign, the employee explained.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"We all left these big corporations to move fa=
st and build exciting things," the employee said. "The bureaucracy of somet=
hing as big as Microsoft is soul crushing."</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The nice thing about signing an open letter sa=
ying =E2=80=9Cif you don=E2=80=99t hire back Sam Altman, we will all quit a=
nd go work at Microsoft=E2=80=9D is that no one can=C2=A0<em>enforce=C2=A0<=
/em>it. If OpenAI=E2=80=99s board didn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0hire back Sam Altman,=
 the people who signed that letter could have stayed at OpenAI,<a class=3D"=
footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impo=
rtant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0or gone to Microsoft, or gone to any of the other companies with =
AI teams that were <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/33617633.284401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlaW5mb3JtYXRpb24uY29tL2FydGljbGVzL29wZW=
5haXMtcml2YWxzLXJ1c2gtdG8tcG9hY2gtb3BlbmFpLXN0YWZmLWFmdGVyLWFsdG1hbi1vdXN0Z=
XI_cmM9MWJkaTVo/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB20025d9e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> salivating</a> =
over OpenAI=E2=80=99s possible employee exodus. Or work at McKinsey, for th=
at matter, or Roblox,=C2=A0or backpack across Europe. Absolutely not a bind=
ing commitment at all, and a seller=E2=80=99s market.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I never really interpreted the OpenAI staff le=
tter to mean =E2=80=9Cwe are psyched to go work at Microsoft.=E2=80=9D I in=
terpreted it to=C2=A0mean something like: =E2=80=9COpenAI <em>consists</em>=
 primarily of (1) Sam Altman, (2) the rest of the employees and (3) a bunch=
 of Microsoft cloud servers. The board of directors of OpenAI, which as a t=
echnical matter <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33=
617633.284401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jMtMTEtMjAvd2hvLWNvbnRyb2xzLW9wZW5haT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjA3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1=
dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEyMDcmdXR=
tX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB06196090" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  h=
as a lot of control</a> over the corporate form of OpenAI, is not itself a =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33617633.284401/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjEvb3Blb=
mFpLWlzLWEtc3RyYW5nZS1ub25wcm9maXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTIwNzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRt=
X21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjA3JnV0bV9=
jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB27d72060" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  part=
icularly important component</a> of OpenAI, and as a practical matter has n=
o real control over <em>what matters</em>. If the board fires Altman, then =
OpenAI =E2=80=94 meaning the people who do the work =E2=80=94=C2=A0will mov=
e somewhere else; the board will be left talking to itself, while the actua=
l beating heart of OpenAI will be elsewhere. It is convenient for that else=
where to be somewhere with a bunch of Microsoft servers, so, sure, we=E2=80=
=99ll sit at desks in Microsoft=E2=80=99s office. But Altman will be in cha=
rge, and all of the day-to-day job relationships will be the same, and we=
=E2=80=99ll just do the same job with the same people in a different room. =
And sure probably someone will have to give us health insurance and an ID c=
ard to get into the building, and <em>ugh fine=C2=A0</em>that will be Micro=
soft, but it=E2=80=99s not like we=E2=80=99ll <em>really</em> work at Micro=
soft; we=E2=80=99ll just work at OpenAI-in-Exile.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not sure that that was=C2=A0an entirely r=
ealistic thing to think. Like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">OpenAI also consists of some intellec=
tual property, contracts, etc. that the board would mostly retain control o=
ver.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There would probably be=
=C2=A0<em>some=C2=A0</em>friction on the way out the door; some of the empl=
oyees who signed the letter would in fact go work at competing AI companies=
, or stay at OpenAI, meaning that you couldn=E2=80=99t just seamlessly recr=
eate the exact same work relationships at OpenAI-in-Exile that you had at O=
penAI the week before.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It does see=
m unlikely that Microsoft would just give you desk space and ID cards and s=
ervers and not meddle=C2=A0<em>at all=C2=A0</em>in your day-to-day working =
life, though I=E2=80=99m sure they promised Altman something close to that.=
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I do think it was correct as a diagnosis o=
f the limits of the board=E2=80=99s power: The company consists essentially=
=C2=A0of its employees, and if they are loyal to Altman then they can cut t=
he board out of things. And anyway it was realistic enough to work as a blu=
ff.</p>
