<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I read a lot of cases against people accused o=
f doing=C2=A0financial crimes, and prosecutors always love to point out wha=
t the criminals=C2=A0spent their ill-gotten money on. There is generally a =
large gambling component (on options trades, crypto or sports betting); oft=
en=C2=A0people who steal money in one part of their lives do so because the=
y are blowing money on bad trades in another part of their lives.=C2=A0And =
there are some typical luxury things: cars, kitchen remodels, whole houses,=
 vacations, yachts or jets (for the really big crimes), watches, etc. So, I=
 mean, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33617633.28=
4401/aHR0cHM6Ly90aGVhdGhsZXRpYy5jb20vNTExODMwOC8yMDIzLzEyLzA2L2phY2tzb252aW=
xsZS1qYWd1YXJzLWVtcGxveWVlLXRoZWZ0LWFtaXQtcGF0ZWwvP2FjY2Vzc190b2tlbj01MjY3N=
zQ0JnJlZGlyZWN0ZWQ9MQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeae38e3b" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> standard<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A former Jacksonville Jaguars empl=
oyee is accused of stealing more than $22 million from the franchise from 2=
019 to 2023 by exploiting the organization=E2=80=99s virtual credit card pr=
ogram, and he used that money to buy, among other items, two vehicles, a co=
ndominium and a designer watch worth over $95,000. Some of that money was a=
lso allegedly used to purchase cryptocurrency and place bets with online ga=
mbling sites.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I don=E2=80=99t think I=E2=80=99ve ever se=
en this before?</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The court filing states that Patel=
 =E2=80=9Cused the proceeds of this scheme, in whole or part, to place bets=
 with online gambling websites; to purchase a condominium in Ponte Vedra Be=
ach, Florida; to pay for personal travel for himself and friends (including=
 chartering private jets and booking luxury hotels and private rental resid=
ences); to acquire a new Tesla Model 3 sedan and Nissan pickup truck; <stro=
ng>to lodge a retainer with a criminal defense law firm</strong>; and to pu=
rchase cryptocurrency, non-fungible tokens, electronics, sports memorabilia=
, a country club membership, spa treatments, concerts and sporting event ti=
ckets, home furnishings and luxury wrist watches.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">(Emphasis added.) He gave some money to a law =
firm to pay for his criminal defense in advance? On the one hand, this stri=
kes me as practical: In a lot of white-collar cases, the first thing the pr=
osecutors do is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33=
617633.284401/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZm9yYmVzLmNvbS9zaXRlcy9zYXJhaGVtZXJzb24vMjAyM=
y8wMy8yOS9zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1sZWdhbC1mZWVzLWZ1bmRlZC1ieS1hbGFtZWRhLW1v=
bmV5LWdpZnRlZC10by1mYXRoZXItam9lLWJhbmttYW4vP3NoPTc1YTY2MzMzZjU3NQ/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBdd7c9c08" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> freeze the allegedly stolen assets</a>,=
 which can make it tough to pay your lawyers; paying the lawyers=C2=A0first=
, before you get arrested,=C2=A0is an interesting way to get around that pr=
oblem. (Not legal advice! May not work!)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, if you are stealing money, =
and your plans for the money include =E2=80=9Cpay for my legal defense afte=
r I get arrested,=E2=80=9D isn=E2=80=99t there a flaw in your plan? Shouldn=
=E2=80=99t you just not do any of that? Me, if I were going to steal the mo=
ney, I=E2=80=99d want to have a pretty solid plan for not getting arrested.=
 Stealing the money and not=C2=A0getting arrested seems optimal, and <em>no=
t=C2=A0</em>stealing the money and not getting arrested is also fine, but s=
tealing the money and getting arrested seems like a very bad outcome even i=
f you have=C2=A0prepaid lawyers? There=E2=80=99s only so much the lawyers c=
an do for you? Because you stole the money?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess you could make a rational decision lik=
e =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m gonna have a lot of fun gambling, golfing, wearing n=
ice watches, flying on chartered jets and going to the spa, and=C2=A0<em>th=
en=C2=A0</em>I=E2=80=99m going to have the best criminal defense money can =
buy, and then I=E2=80=99m going to go to prison, and the utility I get from=
 the golf and spa treatments now will more than outweigh the utility I lose=
 from=C2=A0prison later.=E2=80=9D This is not at all a decision I would eve=
r make, but I=C2=A0do<em>=C2=A0</em>read a lot of financial crime cases, an=
d it sure seems like some people have a different utility function. People =
really like watches.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also what do you=C2=A0<em>tell=C2=A0</em>the l=
awyers when you hire them? =E2=80=9CHello, I am a fine upstanding citizen w=
ho has never been accused of a crime, but here=E2=80=99s a million dollars =
just in case=E2=80=9D? =E2=80=9CHello, I=E2=80=99m doing some big crimes an=
d I haven=E2=80=99t been caught yet, but I=C2=A0would like you to represent=
 me when I do get caught, let me send you some of the proceeds of my crimes=
=E2=80=9D?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-co=
lor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a> Awkward situation for them.</p>
